A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Cornelius Lashon Taylor; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Cornelius Lashon Taylor on January 16, 2025; and
4 WHEREAS, Cornelius Lashon Taylor was born on October 8, 1978, in Walton County,
5 Georgia, and for over a decade, he was a cherished presence in the Old Fourth Ward
6 neighborhoods, particularly on Old Wheat Street; and
7 WHEREAS, he demonstrated a lifelong passion for the arts, expressing himself through
8 music, poetry, and visual art, and as a young child, he had a special love for the flute, often
9 playing melodies that resonated with his soul; and
10 WHEREAS, he was an avid reader who immersed himself in science fiction, murder
11 mysteries, and rap lyrics, finding inspiration in literature and the spoken word; and
12 WHEREAS, a man of deep and abiding faith, Cornelius Lashon Taylor participated in
13 community events and attended services at Ebenezer Baptist Church; and
